verbose_text: In the CSF of patients with multi-infarction dementia or stroke, there is an increased level of ET-1, indicating that ET-1 might play a role in the cognitive deficits related to stroke [XREF_BIBR] MicroRNAs (miRNAs) are noncoding, small RNAs (21 to 25 nucleotides in length) which are supposed to regulate gene activity via accelerating mRNA degradation and/or inducing translational repression, leading to downregulation of target mRNA or protein expression [XREF_BIBR].
